RUB fillets with tarragon and pepper. MELT 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook fillets 4 to 5 minutes on each side, or to desired degree of doneness. Remove from skillet, and keep warm. MELT remaining 3 tablespoons butter in skillet. Add mushrooms, and saute 3 to 4 minutes, or until tender. Add wine, and cook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring to loosen particles from bottom of skillet. Stir in sour cream. Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese into sauce, stirring until melted. ARRANGE fillets on a serving platter, and drizzle with sauce. Sprinkle with remaining cheese, and garnish, if desired.